            How Apollo 8 Astronauts took the famous 'Earthrise' photograph
            In December 1968 Apollo 8 went into orbit around the Moon.  However, the astronauts on board were more impressed by the sight of the Earth rising in the distance than by their close-up view of the lunar surface. Colonel Frank Borman, Commander of Apollo 8, remembers the flight.Witness: The stories of our times told by the people who were there. 
                
                        12 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
